<br>
What if there were a new enchanter spell in PoP, that when many people (30+?) are in linked groups, they can cast a massive c3 upgrade that only lasts 5-10 minutes, with a rather long recast time.  Something that would make everyones mana regen at around 50-100 per tick.<br>
<br>
This could very possibly remove the need for mod rod duty entirely.  And with a prohibitively long recast time, high mana cost, and requirement of a minimum number of linked groups,  short buff duration, and possibly expensive reagent like a diamond,  it would not unbalance normal game play.  IE, it would certainly NOT be worth using in a normal exp or loot group.<br>
<br>
I dunno what verant would consider &quot;balanced&quot; numbers... but off the top of my head something like this:<br>
<br>
Casting time: 30 seconds<br>
Allowable targets: Group+linked groups (so it can be MGBed)<br>
Recast time: 30 minutes to 1 or 2 real hours<br>
Reagent: Something expensive like a diamond.<br>
Effect: 50-100 mana per tick for 5-10 minutes<br>
Stacking: Let it stack with c3<br>
Manacost: 100% of enchanters mana? Or maybe just 3000, that way one would have to be at least decently equipped to use it<br>
Level to scribe: 60, or AA ability (5 or 9 points needed).<br>
<br>
<br>
Or, verant could do a bunch of calculations to make a mana regen spell that would simulate 3-5 mages in a mana making group with a shammy for different numbers.  But with the end goal being that current encounters can be done with the current average number of clercs (5-10) but where mages would actually nuke instead.<br>
<br>
I would just hope that if a spell like this was implemented, guilds wont be like oh well we can just use less clerics now and keep the mages on mod rod duty.  I doubt enchanters would complain much about this spell.. certainly not as much as mages do about rods. <p><img src="http://image1ex.villagephotos.com/extern/519420.jpg"> </a><p>
